# intersection.rules
# Austerity DSL — Traffic intersection controller — Junction 14

AUSTERITY 0.1

# ----------------------------------------------------------------
# DEFINE block - aliases for phase name string literals
#
# These aliases exist only in this source file.
# The parser expands them before any rule is evaluated.
# The engine and the audit log always use the full string values.
#
# Convetion: aliases are UPPERCASE to distinguish them visually
# from state keys (which are lowercase_snake_case).
# ----------------------------------------------------------------

DEFINE
    NSG = "NORTH_SOUTH_GREEN"
    NSY = "NORTH_SOUTH_YELLOW"
    EWG = "EAST_WEST_GREEN"
    EWY = "EAST_WEST_YELLOW"
    AR = "ALL_RED"
END

#
# This file defines the decision logic for a four-way autonomous
# traffic intersection. It is the complete rule set for the MVP demo.
#
# Rules are evaluated in the order they are declared.
# If two rules write to the same key in the same step,
# the rule declared LAST takes precedence.
#
# The phase cycle under normal conditions is:
#
#   NORTH_SOUTH_GREEN
#         |
#   NORTH_SOUTH_YELLOW
#         |
#   ALL_RED  (clearance = true)   <-- vehicles clear the intersection
#         |
#   EAST_WEST_GREEN
#         |
#   EAST_WEST_YELLOW
#         |
#   ALL_RED  (clearance = true)   <-- vehicles clear the intersection
#         |
#   NORTH_SOUTH_GREEN  (and so on)
#
# ALL_RED has two distinct meanings:
#
#   clearance = true  — normal interval between phase transitions.
#                       All directions hold red briefly so vehicles
#                       already in the intersection can clear safely.
#
#   emergency = true  — an emergency vehicle is approaching.
#                       All directions hold red until emergency clears.
#
# These two conditions are mutually exclusive by design.
#
# Rules: 11 total
#   Section 1 — Normal phase rotation   (6 rules)
#   Section 2 — Queue pressure          (3 rules)
#   Section 3 — Emergency response      (2 rules)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------


# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# SECTION 1 — Normal phase rotation
#
# These six rules advance the lights through the standard cycle.
# Yellow phases transition to an all-red clearance interval before
# the opposing direction receives a green signal.
#
# The clearance flag is set to true when entering ALL_RED and back
# back to false when leaving it. This keeps the # emergency rules  in
# Section 3 unambiguous - they only act when clearance = false.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

RULE north_south_green_to_yellow
WHEN phase = NSG AND cycle_timer = 0
THEN
    phase       = NSY
    cycle_timer = 5
END

RULE north_south_yellow_to_clearance
WHEN phase = NSY AND cycle_timer = 0
THEN
    phase       = AR
    clearance   = true
    cycle_timer = 3
END

RULE clearance_to_east_west_green
WHEN phase = AR AND clearance = true AND cycle_timer = 0
THEN
    phase       = EWG
    clearance   = false
    cycle_timer = cycle_time
END

RULE east_west_green_to_yellow
WHEN phase = EWG AND cycle_timer = 0
THEN
    phase       = EWY
    cycle_timer = 5
END

RULE east_west_yellow_to_clearance
WHEN phase = EWY AND cycle_timer = 0
THEN
    phase       = AR
    clearance   = true
    cycle_timer = 3
END

RULE clearance_to_north_south_green
WHEN phase = AR AND clearance = true AND cycle_timer = 0
THEN
    phase       = NSG
    clearance   = false
    cycle_timer = cycle_time
END


# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# SECTION 2 — Queue pressure adjustments
#
# Extension rules fire during a green phase when the queue for
# that direcetion is heavy. They add time to cycle_timer, giving
# the heavy direction longer to drain.
#
# Ceiling condition (cycle_timer < 20): each extension rule fires
# at most once or twice per phase. Without a ceiling, the rule
# would add 10 steps every step the queue stayed above treshold,
# growing the timer without bound and starving the other direction.
# 20 was chosen as roughly half of the default cycle_time (45).
#
# Reduction fires when all queues are light, but only during green
# phases. Yellow and clearance phases have fixed safety durations
# and must never be shortened by traffic pressure rules.
# The engine's zero-clamp ensures cycle_timer never goes negative
# even if this rule fires repeatedly near the end of a phase.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

RULE extend_north_south_on_heavy_load
WHEN phase = NSG AND north_queue > 10 AND cycle_timer < 20
THEN
    cycle_timer = cycle_timer + 10
END

RULE extend_east_west_on_heavy_load
WHEN phase = EWG AND east_queue > 10 AND cycle_timer < 20
THEN
    cycle_timer = cycle_timer + 10
END

RULE reduce_cycle_on_low_traffic
WHEN (phase = NSG OR phase = EWG) AND north_queue < 3 
    AND south_queue < 3 AND east_queue < 3 AND west_queue < 3
THEN
    cycle_timer = cycle_timer - 5
END

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# SECTION 3 — Emergency response
#
# emergency_override fires every step that emergency = true.
# It forces ALL_RED, zeroes the timer and keeps clearance = false
# — distinguishing this emergency hold from a normal clearance
# interval. No rotation rule can fire while this is active,
# because they all test for specific phase or clearance = true.
#
# emergency_recovery fires on the first step after the emergency
# flag clears. Its condition is:
#   emergency = false AND phase = AR AND clearance = false
#
# The clearance = false guard is what makes this unambiguous.
# During a normal clearance interval, clearance = true, so this
# rule cannot fire. After an emergency, clearance remains false
# (set by emergency_override), so this rule fires exactly once
# on the step the emergency ends. This is the intended behaviour.
#
# Declaration order note: emergency_override is declared before
# emergency_recovery. Because last_declared wins on key conflicts,
# recovery takes precedence if both were somehow simultaneously
# true - which cannot happen by construction, but the ordering
# is documented here for future maintainability.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

RULE emergency_override
WHEN emergency = true
THEN
    phase       = AR
    clearance   = false
    cycle_timer = 0
END

RULE emergency_recovery
WHEN emergency = false AND phase = AR AND clearance = false
THEN
    phase       = NSG
    cycle_timer = cycle_time
END
